'''Sidney Smith''' (February 28, 1894 – July 4, 1928), known on-screen as '''Sid Smith''', was an [[United States|American]] [[actor]].  He acted in and directed many [[silent film]]s.  He died of alcohol poisoning from bad liquor.[[File:Charles Dorety & Sid Smith - Aug 1919 EH.jpg|thumb|275px|right|Charles Dorety and Sid Smith in an unidentified 1919 comedy short film]]
